[There are now a total of 978 cases of listeriosis, including 183 deaths, reported since January 2017 in this outbreak in South Africa linked to contaminated ready-to-eat meat produced by Tiger Brands's Enterprise factory in the Limpopo capital, Polokwane. More cases are expected, despite the recall, because of the long incubation period of listeriosis of up to 70 days. In addition, contaminated product may still be in the refrigerators of some people unaware of the situation. - Mod.ML

